title: One dead and five injured after multi-storey car park collapses in New York
description: One person is dead and five people have been injured after a multi-storey car park collapsed in New York City.

title: 'I'm terrified for his life': Vladimir Kara-Murza's wife vows to fight for his freedom after he is jailed in Russia
description: The wife of a dual British-Russian citizen jailed for treason says she is "terrified for his life" but will "fight for him for as long as it takes".

title: Khartoum resident says paramilitaries held her at gunpoint and threatened to rape her
description: A civilian resident in Sudan's capital Khartoum has told how paramilitaries threatened her with rape and held her family at gunpoint as they looted her home.

title: NASA satellite to fall to Earth tomorrow - but what is the likelihood it will hurt someone?
description: An old NASA satellite is expected to fall to Earth this week, but experts say chances that it will pose any danger are low.

title: Bear that killed runner captured amid row over animal's fate
description: A bear that mauled a runner to death has been captured in Italy.

title: Hillary Clinton: Trump cannot win election - but Biden will
description: Hillary Clinton has told Sky News that Donald Trump will not win the next election - and Joe Biden will be re-elected whoever the Republican candidate is.

title: Detained US reporter appears in court in Russia
description: A Russian court has rejected Wall Street Journal reporter Evan Gershkovich's appeal against his pre-trial detention.

title: AI-made song featuring voices of Drake and The Weeknd removed from streaming services
description: A song featuring the cloned voices of Drake and The Weeknd - using AI technology - has been removed from various streaming sites.

title: 'Pristine' coral reef discovered
description: A coral reef with flourishing marine life has been discovered off Ecuador's Galapagos Islands.

title: More than $2.6m raised for black teen shot in head after going to wrong house
description: A fundraiser for Ralph Yarl, the black teenager who was shot in the head in Missouri, has raised more than $2.6m (£2.1m).

title: Putin visits occupied Luhansk and Kherson regions of Ukraine
description: Vladimir Putin has visited occupied areas of Ukraine that Russia illegally annexed last year, the Kremlin has said.

title: BTS band member begins mandatory military service in South Korea
description: Another member of the South Korean boy band BTS has started his mandatory military service.

title: US embassy convoy fired upon in Sudan
description: A US embassy convoy in Sudan was fired upon in a "reckless" and "irresponsible" incident, the US secretary of state said.

title: China economy grows at faster than expected pace
description: China's economy grew at a faster-than-expected pace in the first quarter of the year, according to its official figures, following the end of strict COVID curbs at the end of 2022.

title: Photography award winner declines prize after admitting image was created using AI
description: The winner of a major photography award has turned down the prize after admitting the image he submitted was created by artificial intelligence.
